address.description: Get address of currently executing account.

balance.description: Get balance of the given account.

blockhash.description: Get the hash of one of the 256 most recent complete blocks.

callcode.description: Message-call into this account with alternative account's code.

calldatacopy.description: Copy input data in current environment to memory. This pertains to the input data passed with the message call instruction or transaction.

calldataload.description: Get input data of current environment.

calldatasize.description: Get size of input data in current environment.

caller.description: Get caller address.This is the address of the account that is directly responsible for this execution.

callvalue.description: Get deposited value by the instruction/transaction responsible for this execution.

codecopy.description: Copy code running in current environment to memory.

codesize.description: Get size of code running in current environment.

create.description: Create a new account with associated code.

create2.description: Create a new account with associated code. (Constantinople)

delegatecall.description: Similar to CALLCODE except that it propagates the sender and value from the parent scope to the child scope

extcodecopy.description: Copy an account's code to memory.

extcodesize.description: Get size of an account's code.

gas.description: Get the amount of available gas, including the corresponding reduction

gasprice.description: Get price of gas in current environment.

jumpdest.description: Mark a valid destination for jumps.

log0.description: Append log record with no topics.

log1.description: Append log record with one topic.

log2.description: Append log record with two topics.

log3.description: Append log record with three topics.

log4.description: Append log record with four topics.

msize.description: Get the size of active memory in bytes.

pc.description: Get the value of the program counter prior to the increment.

returndatacopy.description: Copy data from the return data buffer.

returndatasize.description: Push the size of the return data buffer onto the stack.

selfdestruct.description: Halt execution and register account for later deletion.

signextend.description: Extend length of two's complement signed integer.

staticcall.description: Call another contract (or itself) while disallowing any modifications to the state during the call.
